<p><strong>English:</strong> The dance consists of two separate ones, said to be a thirteenth century harvest dance and a seventeenth century dance in honor of a deceased lord.</p>

<p><strong>にほんごで:</strong> つぎのひはなまきにわんこそばたべった。</p>

<p><strong>English:</strong> The next day we went to Hanamaki for the local soba-noodle dish, the staff constantly pours the contents of the small bowls into your eating bowl. They only stop pouring when you cover your bowl.</p>

